Known Bugs
----------

== Greek ==

Shifting accentage messes up the paradigms, for 
example:

* πρόβλημα     próvlima
* προβλήματος  provlímatos
* προβλήματα   provlímata
* προβλημάτων  provlimáton

We can't very well split it as: πρ/όβλημα, so I'm
not sure if this accenting is standard, or what
the ambiguity would be if we did the standard "take
in whatever, output /x/" trick.

